KSP: 0.90.0

Problem: None of the mods seem to be working. I read a few areas that suggested that having ksp in program files(x86) or whatever could cause problems along with antivirus's which this was never the case before...but since its broke I took the gamble of trying those out...still doesnt work. Please help!

Mods Installed:

Active Texture Basic 4-3

TweakScale 1.49 I think (whatever version is on KerbalStuff)

Editor Extensions 2.5

Module Manager 2.5.6

Reproduction steps:

Open game, go to build a craft, nothing shows up...all the same options in the editors...no tweakscale on parts...even stock.

This might be your problem. your Frame wont fit. i would like:

:Window size,EG: 1900x600

:FPS(frames per second)(if possible)

:Specs, EG: windows, 500G harddrive space, 4G ram, and etc

Also i recommend uninstalling all your mods. and re-installing ksp.
Update your graphics driver, restart your PC, and do not use -force-opengl or -force-dx11

Thanks guys! I will have to try those next time i got some free time. Computer has been kind of crappy as of late so been uninstalling a bunch of stuff. But thanks for the help and will report back when I can
So it did end up being my graphics card...it was on the brink of dying =[ But I got a different one and the above mods seem to be working now Thanks again guys for the insight!
